# {{ title }} — GLQ {{ bpw_label }}

**GLQ ({{ "%.1f"|format(avg_bpw) }} bits/weight)** quantization of [`{{ base_model }}`](https://huggingface.co/{{ base_model }}) using an **E8-lattice codebook + randomized Hadamard transform (RHT) + LDLQ**. Weights stay compressed in memory and are dequantized on the fly by fused CUDA kernels.

> **Where GLQ shines:** the size-vs-accuracy win is strongest at **2–4 bits/weight**. {% if avg_bpw > 4.05 %}At {{ "%.1f"|format(avg_bpw) }} bpw the weight savings are modest — the bigger win at this precision is pairing it with the **E8 KV cache** (≈4× smaller KV cache → much longer context / more concurrency in the same VRAM).{% else %}For even more headroom, combine it with the **E8 KV cache** (≈4× smaller KV cache → longer context in the same VRAM).{% endif +%}

- **Base model:** [`{{ base_model }}`](https://huggingface.co/{{ base_model }})
