## How GLQ works

Each group of 8 weights is rounded to the nearest **E8 lattice** point (a Golay/Leech-family shell codebook). A **randomized Hadamard transform** whitens the weights so the Hessian is near-diagonal, and **LDLQ** error feedback propagates rounding error across columns. {{ stages_blurb }}

